modules.description: Detects MIME types from file content using magic number signatures, supports parsing and matching against a database of known file types. Operates on byte sequences and file paths, providing accurate type identification for binary and text data. Used to determine appropriate handlers for file uploads, content negotiation in web servers, and data validation in network protocols.

Provides a function to execute a given action within a database context, returning a result that may include a string or an error message. Operates with Lwt threads, databases, and metadata structures. Used to run database operations asynchronously while handling potential errors and optional outputs.
